The paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for image classification and mapping, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The study also involves geographic information systems (GIS) and remote sensing, which could place it under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of comparing the results with the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) crop data layer (CDL) products.
